issues.title: Intermediate Shaft (IMS) Bearing Failure
issues.description: The intermediate shaft bearing can fail catastrophically, causing complete engine failure. While less common in 987.2 models compared to earlier generations, it still occurs and can result in total engine replacement.
issues.fix_description: Complete engine rebuild or replacement, IMS bearing replacement if caught early
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, oil analysis, consider preventive IMS bearing replacement

issues.title: Direct Injection Carbon Buildup
issues.description: Direct injection engines accumulate carbon deposits on intake valves over time, reducing performance and causing rough idle. This is inherent to the DFI system design.
issues.fix_description: Walnut blasting or chemical cleaning of intake valves
issues.prevention: Regular high RPM driving, quality fuel, periodic intake cleaning service

issues.title: PDK Transmission Mechatronic Unit Failure
issues.description: The PDK transmission control unit (mechatronic unit) can fail, causing transmission to go into limp mode or fail to shift properly. Common in higher mileage vehicles.
issues.fix_description: Replace or rebuild mechatronic unit, transmission software update
issues.prevention: Regular transmission service, avoid aggressive shifting when cold

issues.title: Water Pump Failure
issues.description: Electric water pump can fail prematurely, leading to engine overheating. The pump housing can crack or the impeller can fail.
issues.fix_description: Replace water pump and thermostat, flush cooling system
issues.prevention: Regular cooling system maintenance, monitor coolant levels

issues.title: Clutch Slave Cylinder Failure (Manual)
issues.description: Clutch slave cylinder can leak internally, causing clutch pedal to stick to floor or feel spongy. Common wear item on manual transmission cars.
issues.fix_description: Replace clutch slave cylinder and bleed hydraulic system
issues.prevention: Regular brake fluid changes, avoid riding the clutch

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Failure
issues.description: Internal door handle mechanism can break, preventing door from opening from inside. Plastic components become brittle over time.
issues.fix_description: Replace door handle mechanism and related linkages
issues.prevention: Gentle operation of door handles, regular lubrication

issues.title: Oxygen Sensor Failure
issues.description: Oxygen sensors can fail prematurely, causing poor fuel economy, rough idle, and emissions test failures. Common issue with high mileage vehicles.
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel, regular maintenance, avoid engine misfires

issues.title: Coolant Pipe Leaks
issues.description: Plastic coolant pipes and connections can develop leaks over time, particularly at joints and elbows. Heat cycling causes plastic to become brittle.
issues.fix_description: Replace leaking coolant pipes and fittings
issues.prevention: Regular cooling system inspections, avoid overheating

issues.title: Window Regulator Failure
issues.description: Power window regulators can fail, causing windows to drop unexpectedly or fail to operate. Plastic guides and cables wear out over time.
issues.prevention: Avoid slamming doors, regular window track cleaning

issues.title: Oil Separator (AOS) Failure
issues.description: The air/oil separator can fail, causing oil consumption, smoking, and potential engine damage. Diaphragm inside unit deteriorates over time.
issues.fix_description: Replace air/oil separator and clean intake system
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, avoid extended idle periods

issues.title: Radiator Fan Failure
issues.description: Electric radiator fans can fail due to motor burnout or control module issues, leading to overheating in stop-and-go traffic.
issues.fix_description: Replace radiator fan motor and/or control module
issues.prevention: Regular cooling system maintenance, keep radiator clean

editorial.tagline: The sweet-spot Porsche that proves perfection exists
editorial.hero_blurb: The 987.2 Cayman S represents Porsche's mid-engine masterpiece at its absolute peak. With 320 horsepower from a naturally aspirated flat-six and the most balanced chassis in the lineup, this is the Cayman that made Stuttgart nervous about overshadowing the 911.
editorial.essence: This is the Goldilocks Porsche - not too much power to overwhelm, not too little to disappoint, but just right for pure driving bliss. The 987.2 generation fixed every weakness of the original while preserving all the magic that made the Cayman special.
editorial.heritage: Born from Porsche's desire to create the ultimate mid-engine sports car, the Cayman evolved from the Boxster hardtop concept. The 987.2 generation (2009-2012) represents the final flowering of this first-generation platform before turbocharging arrived.
editorial.design_philosophy: Pure function over form, with every line serving aerodynamics and cooling. The designers created a shape that was unmistakably Porsche while establishing the Cayman's own visual identity - muscular haunches, dramatic side intakes, and perfect proportions that scream mid-engine athleticism.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not a factory racer initially, the Cayman quickly proved its worth in amateur motorsport and one-make series. The platform's inherent balance made it a favorite among track day enthusiasts and club racers worldwide.
editorial.engine_character: The 3.4L flat-six is a rev-happy jewel that builds power linearly to its 7400 RPM redline. It's mechanical, urgent, and utterly addictive - the last great naturally aspirated Porsche engine before forced induction took over.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 6-speed manual is mechanical perfection with short, precise throws and a clutch that communicates every nuance. Each gear change feels like operating Swiss clockwork - deliberate, satisfying, and absolutely connected to the drivetrain.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Telepathic balance defines the experience. The mid-engine layout provides incredible stability under braking and neutral handling that flatters any driver while rewarding those who push harder. It changes direction with the precision of a surgeon's scalpel.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulic perfection that delivers unfiltered road surface information directly to your palms. Weighting is ideal - light enough for parking, heavy enough for confidence at speed, with zero artificial assistance masking the connection to the front wheels.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive stopping power that inspires complete confidence. The brakes are progressive, fade-resistant, and perfectly matched to the chassis dynamics. You can brake later and harder than you ever thought possible.
editorial.sound_signature: A mechanical symphony that growls at idle, wails at redline, and produces the most intoxicating flat-six soundtrack ever created. The sound is visceral, purposeful, and utterly addictive - pure automotive emotion made audible.
editorial.ideal_owner: The driving purist who values connection over comfort, someone who appreciates mechanical perfection and doesn't need back seats or massive trunk space. Perfect for the enthusiast who wants the ultimate weekend warrior.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Daily commuters needing practicality, luxury seekers wanting cushy rides, or badge collectors who need the 911's prestige. This is a driver's car first and foremost.
editorial.buyers_summary: Find the cleanest example possible and buy it immediately - these are future classics that are only appreciating. Focus on maintenance records over mileage, as these engines thrive on regular use and proper care.

expertReviews.title: DRIVEN: Why The Porsche 987.2 Cayman S Is The Perfect ...
pros: Better looking than later generations with more distinct design
320 hp direct injection engine free of IMS issues

expertReviews.verdict: The 987.2 Cayman S offers exceptional value as a sports car at £25,000 - about half the price of a 981 Boxster S. With 320hp, direct injection reliability, and classic Porsche driving dynamics, it delivers most of the thrills of more expensive models. While it has some minor flaws like long gearing and interior rattles, it's a very balanced, practical sports car that responds well to modifications.

cons: Elderly passengers may struggle with entry/exit

expertReviews.verdict: Strong recommendation to buy. The 987.2 Cayman S offers an exceptional complete package combining practicality, performance, and prestige for £11,995. While you can find faster or more practical cars for the money, nothing matches the Cayman's overall balance. The 2.9L flat-six with direct injection provides improved reliability over earlier models, and the conventional power steering delivers superior feel compared to modern electric systems. This particular example has impeccable Porsche dealer service history despite higher mileage.

expertReviews.title: Porsche Cayman S 987.2 REVIEW - did the best just get better ... by Fast and Fun
pros: Fantastic naturally aspirated flat-six engine with linear power delivery
Excellent ride quality that's surprisingly comfortable for daily use
Great driving position and visibility with direct, light steering
Very practical with luggage space in both front and rear compartments
Gen 2 DFI engine eliminates notorious IMS and bore scoring issues
Holds value well and increasingly sought after
cons: Very heavy clutch and gearbox that requires effort
Poor headlights requiring aftermarket bulb upgrades
AC condensers prone to debris damage without protection
Center dash technology feels outdated for age
expertReviews.verdict: The 987.2 Cayman S is described as an excellent sports car that successfully combines performance with daily usability. The reviewer was impressed by the surprisingly comfortable ride quality, fantastic naturally aspirated engine character, and overall practicality. While the heavy gearbox and clutch take adjustment, the car's reliability improvements over Gen 1 models and strong value retention make it highly desirable. The reviewer suggests it could easily serve as both a weekend toy and daily commuter.

expertReviews.title: 2009 Porsche Cayman S (987.2 vs. 987.1) - POV Driving ... by TheTopher
pros: No IMS bearing failure - more reliable than 987.1
320 hp vs 295 hp - more power than previous generation
Excellent handling with telepathic steering
Practical with dual trunks for daily driving
Great value sports car for around $30k
Excellent build quality - 116k mile example drives like new
Perfect power-to-weight ratio under 3000 lbs
cons: Some interior button wear issues still present
expertReviews.verdict: The 987.2 Cayman S represents 'Peak Cayman' - solving the IMS bearing issues of the 987.1 while adding more power (320hp vs 295hp) and refined aesthetics. Despite costing $10-15k more than a 987.1, it offers exceptional reliability, telepathic steering, and practical dual-trunk layout. The reviewer considers it the best sports car value at $30k, preferring it over newer 981/718 generations and even 911s. However, buyers must weigh the premium against 987.1 models that can have IMS bearing serviced for much less.

expertReviews.verdict: The 987.2 Cayman S Sport is described as 'basically flawless' with superb handling, great engine character, and excellent practicality. However, reliability concerns with the M97 engine and limited edition pricing make the regular 987 S a better value proposition for most buyers. The reviewer considers it all the car you'd ever need if you only need two seats.

pros: Excellent value proposition at $14-18k range

Mid-engine layout with decent power
Manual transmission available
Well-built interior that has aged well
Functional and focused design
Great engineering details like hidden cup holders
cons: Not particularly fast compared to modern standards
Base model only has 5-speed manual vs 6-speed in S
expertReviews.verdict: The 987 Cayman is described as a phenomenal car that Doug recommends to basically everyone interested in a fun sports car in this price range. Despite not being the fastest or rarest, it offers tremendous value as a well-engineered mid-engine Porsche with surprising practicality and excellent design details. The combination of affordability, proper manual transmission, and classic Porsche engineering makes it an ideal choice for sports car enthusiasts.
